RED COMET was no threat. TOYI with the second flight two wide, gave way in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: THISTLEDOWN RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 52. Maiden Special Weight Purse 26400. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DEFENDER GAL stumbled inward bumping DANCE MY WAY at the start, dueled for the lead along the inside and wore down rivals in a game effort. CATCHMENOW was bumped at the start, checked behind the winner leaving the chute, saved ground early then rallied determinedly four wide through the stretch in a determined effort. SHEWEARSMYRING drifted in entering the main track, saved ground and finished with good courage along the rail. SISTER CODE was shut off along the rail at the elven sixteenths pole causing her rider to check hard, trailed into the stretch then closed a gap late outside in the six path. HOLY SKULL battled with the winner two wide through the turn and was outfinished. DANCE MY WAY was bumped hard at the start, checked leaving the chute, rallied three wide to make the lead nearing the quarter pole, battled until mid stretch then came up empty. TRAMA QUEEN also bumped hard at the start, checked leaving the chute and was through after a half. THE RIDER OF CATCHMENOW LODGED A CLAIM OF FOUL AGAINST THE RIDER OF THE WINNER FOR ALLEGED INTERFERENCE LEAVING THE CHUTE. ALSO THE RIDER OF SISTER CODE LODGED A CLAIM OF FOUL AGAINST THE RIDER OF SHEWEASMYRING FOR ALLEGED INTERFERENCE SHORTLY AFTER THE START. AFTER REVIEW BOTH CLAIMS OF FOUL WERE DISALLOWED AND THE STEWARDS UPHELD THE ORIGINAL ORDER OF FINISH.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Greg Veit Scarlet and Gray S. THISTLEDOWN RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 88. Stakes Purse 75000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE-YEAR-OLDS AND UPWARD REGISTERED OHIO FOALS (WHICH REFLECTS $26,250 FROM THE OHIO THOROUGHBRED FUND). Foaled in the State of Ohio as per requirements set forth by the Ohio State Racing Commission. Nomination fee of $50. $262 to enter with an additional $488 to start, with a purse of $75,000, of which 60% to the winner, 20% to second, 10% to third, 5% to fourth, 3% to fifth and 2% to sixth. Nominations Close Monday, September 25th, 2023. Weights: Three-year-olds 119 lbs; Older12 3 lbs. Non-Winners of $30,000 Twice in 2022-2023 allowed 2 lbs; A Race other Maiden, Claiming, Optional or Starter since April 5th, 2023 allowed 4 lbs; A Race other Maiden, Claiming, Optional or Starter since October 5th, 2022 allowed 6 lbsStarters to bbe named through the entry box Monday, October 2nd, 2023. A Trophy will be presented to the Winning Owner. This stake will not split. In the event more than fourteen (14) horses pass the entry box at the time of closing of entries, preference will be given
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BACK TO OHIO had good early speed along the inside, waited for racing room behind a trio of horses through the turn, angled out and split rivals two wide entering the stretch, shifted inside the leader, surged along the rail and proved best under confident handling. CANDLELIGHT HOURS pressed the pace two wide into the turn, made the lead, drifted to the four path at the top of the stretch then inward through deep stretch and couldn't handle the winner. TIVIS allowed to settle, had a mild late rally in the four path. WINE ME UP BABY away alertly, set the pace near the inside until mid turn, remained a sharp threat into the stretch and weakened late. R THREE ANGELS was taken outside shortly after the start and failed to menace. AUNT BEE was no factor. KICHI KITSU stalked the leaders four wide down the backstretch, loomed boldly three wide entering the turn then came up empty.
